## Code: Format Output (final node)

Returns only a small summary — never the raw `forecastData`:

```javascript
const upload = $input.first().json;
const genNode = $('Generate Excel Workbook').first().json;
const computeNode = $('Compute Financials v4').first().json;
let keyFindings = null;
try { keyFindings = JSON.parse(computeNode.output).keyFindings; } catch(e) {}

return [{ json: { output: JSON.stringify({
  success: true,
  fileName: genNode.fileName,
  property: genNode.property,
  period: genNode.period,
  driveFileId: upload.id || null,
  driveLink: upload.webViewLink || upload.webContentLink || null,
  tabs: genNode.tabs,
  keyFindings: keyFindings
}) } }];
```

